00:17:46,525 --> 00:17:49,987
I'd like to thank you all
for coming to my wedding.

252
00:17:50,070 --> 00:17:53,365
First, I better go in there
and propose to the girl.

253
00:17:55,784 --> 00:17:58,620
And you, LeFou, now,
when Belle and I come out that door...

254
00:17:58,662 --> 00:18:01,290
I know. I know. I strike up the band!

255
00:18:04,960 --> 00:18:06,920
-Not yet.
-Sorry.

256
00:18:19,266 --> 00:18:22,186
Gaston, what a pleasant surprise.

257
00:18:22,269 --> 00:18:25,564
Isn't it, though?
I'm just full of surprises.

258
00:18:25,647 --> 00:18:27,482
You know, Belle,
there's not a girl in town

259
00:18:27,524 --> 00:18:30,152
who wouldn't love to be in your shoes.

260
00:18:30,194 --> 00:18:31,862
This is the day...

261
00:18:34,948 --> 00:18:37,326
This is the day your dreams come true.

262
00:18:37,409 --> 00:18:40,162
What do you know
about my dreams, Gaston?

263
00:18:40,245 --> 00:18:42,998
Plenty! Here. Picture this.

264
00:18:43,999 --> 00:18:48,879
A rustic hunting lodge,
my latest kill roasting on the fire

265
00:18:48,962 --> 00:18:52,341
and my little wife massaging my feet

266
00:18:52,466 --> 00:18:54,843
while the little ones play on the floor
with the dogs.

267
00:18:54,885 --> 00:18:57,262
-We'll have six or seven.
-Dogs?

268
00:18:57,346 --> 00:18:58,889
No, Belle.

269
00:18:58,972 --> 00:19:01,725
-Strapping boys like me.
-Imagine that.

270
00:19:01,808 --> 00:19:03,143
Do you know who that little wife will be?

271
00:19:03,185 --> 00:19:05,187
-Let me think.
-You, Belle.

272
00:19:05,229 --> 00:19:09,066
Gaston, I'm... I'm speechless.

273
00:19:09,399 --> 00:19:11,568
I really don't know what to say.

274
00:19:11,652 --> 00:19:15,030
-Say you'll marry me.
-I'm very sorry, Gaston, but...

275
00:19:15,864 --> 00:19:18,825
But I just don't deserve you!

276
00:19:33,882 --> 00:19:35,467
So, how'd it go?

277
00:19:36,635 --> 00:19:39,555
I'll have Belle for my wife.

278
00:19:39,596 --> 00:19:42,391
Make no mistake about that.

279
00:19:44,059 --> 00:19:45,269
Touchy.

280
00:19:52,609 --> 00:19:53,986
Is he gone?

281
00:19:55,946 --> 00:19:59,074
Can you imagine?
He asked me to marry him.

282
00:19:59,157 --> 00:20:02,995
Me, the wife of that boorish, brainless...

283
00:20:03,495 --> 00:20:05,414
♪ Madame Gaston

284
00:20:05,455 --> 00:20:07,332
♪ Can't you just see it?

285
00:20:07,416 --> 00:20:09,376
♪ Madame Gaston

286
00:20:09,418 --> 00:20:11,211
♪ His little wife

287
00:20:11,253 --> 00:20:14,756
♪ No, sir, not me, I guarantee it

288
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:19,386
♪ I want much more
♪ than this provincial life

289
00:20:28,353 --> 00:20:33,400
♪ I want adventure
♪ in the great wide somewhere

290
00:20:33,442 --> 00:20:37,279
♪ I want it more than I can tell

291
00:20:38,197 --> 00:20:41,283
♪ And for once it might be grand

292
00:20:41,366 --> 00:20:44,995
♪ To have someone understand

293
00:20:45,787 --> 00:20:52,628
♪ I want so much more
♪ than they've got planned

294
00:20:54,421 --> 00:20:59,468
Philippe! What are you doing here?
Where's... Where's Papa?

295
00:20:59,510 --> 00:21:02,221
Where is he, Philippe?
What happened?

296
00:21:02,304 --> 00:21:05,390
We have to find him.
You have to take me to him.

297
00:21:19,071 --> 00:21:20,822
What is this place?

298
00:21:22,324 --> 00:21:24,326
Philippe, please, steady.

299
00:21:26,328 --> 00:21:27,538
Steady.

300
00:21:31,333 --> 00:21:32,417
Papa!

301
00:21:33,502 --> 00:21:35,796
Couldn't keep quiet, could we?

302
00:21:35,838 --> 00:21:38,340
Just had to invite him to stay,
didn't we?

303
00:21:38,382 --> 00:21:42,803
Serve him tea, sit in the master's chair.
Pet the pooch.

304
00:21:42,845 --> 00:21:44,513
[L]I was trying to be hospitable.

305
00:21:45,973 --> 00:21:47,182
Hello?

306
00:21:47,850 --> 00:21:49,351
Is anyone here?

307
00:21:50,269 --> 00:21:51,436
Hello?

308
00:21:52,771 --> 00:21:55,691
Papa? Papa?

309
00:21:56,650 --> 00:21:58,110
Are you here?

310
00:21:58,735 --> 00:22:01,446
Mama, there's a girl in the castle.

311
00:22:01,530 --> 00:22:04,533
Now, Chip, I'll not have you
making up such wild stories.

312
00:22:04,575 --> 00:22:06,743
Really, Mama. I saw her.

313
00:22:06,827 --> 00:22:09,079
-Not another word. Into the tub.
-But... What?

314
00:22:09,162 --> 00:22:12,207
A girl. I saw a girl in the castle.

315
00:22:12,875 --> 00:22:14,459
See, I told you.

316
00:22:14,877 --> 00:22:19,047
Irresponsible, devil-may-care,
waxy-eared, slack-jawed...

317
00:22:19,089 --> 00:22:20,215
Papa?

318
00:22:21,842 --> 00:22:23,468
Did you see that?

319
00:22:25,387 --> 00:22:28,557
-It's a girl!
-I know it's a girl.

320
00:22:28,599 --> 00:22:31,810
Don't you see? She's the one.
The girl we have been waiting for.

321
00:22:31,894 --> 00:22:34,605
[L]-She has come to break the spell.
[L]-Wait a minute. Wait a minute.

322
00:22:38,525 --> 00:22:39,610
Papa?

323
00:22:41,236 --> 00:22:42,362
Papa?

324
00:22:45,032 --> 00:22:46,950
Hello? Is someone here?

325
00:22:47,701 --> 00:22:50,370
Wait! I'm looking for my father. I...

326
00:22:53,916 --> 00:22:56,627
That's funny.
I'm sure there was someone.

327
00:22:58,754 --> 00:23:00,255
Is anyone here?

328
00:23:00,839 --> 00:23:02,758
-Belle?
-Papa!

329
00:23:05,385 --> 00:23:06,803
How did you find me?

330
00:23:06,887 --> 00:23:09,723
Your hands are like ice.
We have to get you out of there.

331
00:23:09,765 --> 00:23:11,767
Belle, I want you to leave this place.

332
00:23:11,850 --> 00:23:12,976
Who's done this to you?

333
00:23:13,060 --> 00:23:15,562
No time to explain. You must go. Now!

334
00:23:15,604 --> 00:23:17,940
-I won't leave you.
-What are you doing here?

335
00:23:17,981 --> 00:23:19,233
Run, Belle!

336
00:23:19,274 --> 00:23:22,778
-Who's there? Who are you?
-The master of this castle.

337
00:23:23,862 --> 00:23:25,447
I've come for my father.

338
00:23:25,531 --> 00:23:27,783
Please let him out.
Can't you see he's sick?

339
00:23:27,866 --> 00:23:30,118
Then he shouldn't
have trespassed here!

340
00:23:30,160 --> 00:23:32,829
But he could die.
Please, I'll do anything.

341
00:23:32,913 --> 00:23:36,708
There's nothing you can do.
He's my prisoner.

342
00:23:36,792 --> 00:23:39,086
There must be some way I can...

343
00:23:39,962 --> 00:23:41,088
Wait!

344
00:23:46,301 --> 00:23:49,012
-Take me instead.
-You?

345
00:23:50,848 --> 00:23:53,892
You would take his place?

346
00:23:53,976 --> 00:23:56,186
Belle, no!
You don't know what you're doing!

347
00:23:56,270 --> 00:23:59,273
If I did, would you let him go?

348
00:23:59,314 --> 00:24:03,902
Yes. But you must promise
to stay here forever.

349
00:24:06,321 --> 00:24:08,115
Come into the light.

350
00:24:19,835 --> 00:24:22,671
No, Belle! I won't let you do this!

351
00:24:25,674 --> 00:24:27,759
-You have my word.
-Done.

352
00:24:32,014 --> 00:24:35,309
No, Belle, listen to me.
I'm old. I've lived my life.

353
00:24:35,350 --> 00:24:36,393
Wait.

354
00:24:36,476 --> 00:24:37,519
[L]-Belle!
[L]-Wait.

355
00:24:39,062 --> 00:24:41,815
No! Please spare my daughter. Please!

356
00:24:41,857 --> 00:24:45,194
She's no longer your concern.
Take him to the village.

357
00:24:45,277 --> 00:24:48,071
Let me out. Please let me out!

358
00:24:48,155 --> 00:24:52,284
Let me out! Please! Please!

359
00:24:58,123 --> 00:24:59,625
-Master?
-What?

360
00:25:00,334 --> 00:25:03,462
Since the girl is going to be with us
for quite some time,

361
00:25:03,545 --> 00:25:08,258
I was thinking that you might want
to offer her a more comfortable room.

362
00:25:10,219 --> 00:25:11,553
[L]Then again, maybe not.

363
00:25:14,306 --> 00:25:16,558
You didn't even let me say goodbye.

364
00:25:16,642 --> 00:25:18,644
I'll never see him again.

365
00:25:19,228 --> 00:25:21,355
I didn't get to say goodbye.

366
00:25:22,648 --> 00:25:24,566
I'll show you to your room.

367
00:25:24,608 --> 00:25:27,194
My room? But I thought...

368
00:25:27,861 --> 00:25:29,571
You wanna...
You wanna stay in the tower?

369
00:25:29,655 --> 00:25:31,031
[L]-No.
[L]-Then follow me.

370
00:25:52,511 --> 00:25:54,346
Say something to her.

371
00:25:56,181 --> 00:25:59,268
I hope you like it here.

372
00:26:01,895 --> 00:26:03,021
The castle is your home now,

373
00:26:03,105 --> 00:26:06,066
so you can go anywhere you like,
except the west wing.

374
00:26:06,108 --> 00:26:08,777
-What's in the west...
-It's forbidden!

375
00:26:15,826 --> 00:26:19,246
Now, if you need anything,
my servants will attend you.

376
00:26:19,288 --> 00:26:21,498
Dinner. Invite her to dinner.

377
00:26:21,957 --> 00:26:25,752
You will join me for dinner.
That's not a request!

378
00:26:44,313 --> 00:26:46,231
Who does she think she is?

379
00:26:46,315 --> 00:26:48,483
That girl has tangled
with the wrong man.

380
00:26:48,525 --> 00:26:51,612
-No one says no to Gaston.
-Darn right.

381
00:26:51,653 --> 00:26:55,991
Dismissed. Rejected.
Publicly humiliated.

382
00:26:56,033 --> 00:26:57,993
Why, it's more than I can bear.

383
00:26:58,076 --> 00:27:01,496
-More beer?
-What for? Nothing helps.

384
00:27:01,580 --> 00:27:04,666
[L]-I'm disgraced.
[L]-Who, you? Never.

385
00:27:05,167 --> 00:27:08,837
Gaston, you've got
to pull yourself together.

386
00:27:09,254 --> 00:27:12,382
♪ Gosh, it disturbs me
♪ to see you, Gaston

387
00:27:12,424 --> 00:27:15,552
♪ Looking so down in the dumps

388
00:27:15,636 --> 00:27:18,847
♪ Every guy here'd
♪ love to be you, Gaston

389
00:27:18,931 --> 00:27:21,892
♪ Even when taking your lumps

390
00:27:21,975 --> 00:27:25,020
♪ There's no man in town
♪ as admired as you

391
00:27:25,062 --> 00:27:28,607
♪ You're everyone's favorite guy

392
00:27:28,690 --> 00:27:31,944
♪ Everyone's awed
♪ and inspired by you

393
00:27:32,027 --> 00:27:35,072
♪ And it's not very hard

394
00:27:35,155 --> 00:27:38,992
♪ To see why

395
00:27:40,702 --> 00:27:45,290
♪ No one's slick as Gaston

396
00:27:45,374 --> 00:27:46,875
♪ No one's quick as Gaston

397
00:27:46,917 --> 00:27:50,212
♪ No one's neck's
♪ as incredibly thick as Gaston

398
00:27:50,254 --> 00:27:53,924
♪ For there's no man in town
♪ half as manly

399
00:27:54,007 --> 00:27:56,718
♪ Perfect, a pure paragon

400
00:27:56,760 --> 00:28:00,055
♪ You can ask any
♪ Tom, Dick or Stanley

401
00:28:00,097 --> 00:28:05,519
♪ And they'll tell you
♪ whose team they prefer to be on

402
00:28:05,561 --> 00:28:09,815
♪ No one's been like Gaston

403
00:28:09,898 --> 00:28:11,483
♪ A kingpin like Gaston

404
00:28:11,567 --> 00:28:14,778
♪ No one's got a swell cleft
♪ in his chin like Gaston

405
00:28:14,862 --> 00:28:18,699
♪ As a specimen, yes, I'm intimidating

406
00:28:18,782 --> 00:28:21,702
♪ My, what a guy, that Gaston

407
00:28:21,785 --> 00:28:25,122
♪ Give five hurrahs
♪ Give 12 hip-hips

408
00:28:25,205 --> 00:28:29,751
♪ Gaston is the best
♪ and the rest is all drips

409
00:28:30,544 --> 00:28:34,923
♪ No one fights like Gaston

410
00:28:35,007 --> 00:28:36,633
♪ Douses lights like Gaston

411
00:28:36,717 --> 00:28:39,970
♪ In a wrestling match
♪ nobody bites like Gaston

412
00:28:40,053 --> 00:28:43,390
♪ For there's no one
♪ as burly and brawny

413
00:28:43,432 --> 00:28:46,643
♪ As you see, I've got biceps to spare

414
00:28:46,727 --> 00:28:50,439
♪ -Not a bit of him scraggly or scrawny
♪ -That's right

415
00:28:50,522 --> 00:28:53,483
♪ And every last inch of me's
♪ covered with hair

416
00:28:53,567 --> 00:28:56,737
♪ -No one hits like Gaston
♪ -Matches wits like Gaston

417
00:28:56,778 --> 00:29:00,199
♪ In a spitting match
♪ nobody spits like Gaston

418
00:29:00,282 --> 00:29:04,036
♪ I'm especially good at expectorating

419
00:29:04,661 --> 00:29:07,164
♪ Ten points for Gaston

420
00:29:07,247 --> 00:29:10,209
♪ When I was a lad
♪ I ate four dozen eggs

421
00:29:10,292 --> 00:29:13,795
♪ Every morning to help me get large

422
00:29:13,837 --> 00:29:16,882
♪ And now that I'm grown
♪ I eat five dozen eggs

423
00:29:16,965 --> 00:29:22,971
♪ So I'm roughly the size of a barge

424
00:29:23,013 --> 00:29:27,809
♪ No one shoots like Gaston

425
00:29:27,893 --> 00:29:29,520
♪ Makes those beauts like Gaston

426
00:29:29,603 --> 00:29:32,814
♪ Then goes tromping around
♪ wearing boots like Gaston

427
00:29:32,898 --> 00:29:36,860
♪ I use antlers in all of my decorating

428
00:29:36,902 --> 00:29:39,404
♪ My, what a guy

429
00:29:39,488 --> 00:29:45,410
♪ Gaston

430
00:29:49,915 --> 00:29:52,334
-Help! Someone help me!
-Maurice?

431
00:29:52,417 --> 00:29:54,670
Please! Please, I need your help.

432
00:29:54,711 --> 00:29:57,422
He's got her...
He's got her locked in the dungeon.

433
00:29:57,464 --> 00:29:59,508
-Who?
-Belle. We must go.

434
00:29:59,550 --> 00:30:01,301
Not... Not a minute to lose.

435
00:30:01,426 --> 00:30:03,762
Whoa! Slow down, Maurice.

436
00:30:03,846 --> 00:30:06,640
-Who's got Belle locked in a dungeon?
-A beast!

437
00:30:06,682 --> 00:30:09,351
A horrible, monstrous beast!

438
00:30:14,940 --> 00:30:16,692
-Is it a big beast?
-Huge.

439
00:30:16,775 --> 00:30:19,695
-With a long, ugly snout?
-Hideously ugly.

440
00:30:19,778 --> 00:30:23,282
-And sharp, cruel fangs?
-Yes, yes! Will you help me?

441
00:30:23,365 --> 00:30:26,076
All right, old man. We'll help you out.

442
00:30:26,159 --> 00:30:29,913
[L]You will?
[L]Thank you, thank you, thank you.

443
00:30:32,207 --> 00:30:34,543
Crazy old Maurice.

444
00:30:34,585 --> 00:30:37,379
He's always good for a laugh.

445
00:30:38,714 --> 00:30:40,757
Crazy old Maurice?

446
00:30:42,217 --> 00:30:44,636
Crazy old Maurice.

447
00:30:46,013 --> 00:30:49,349
♪ LeFou, I'm afraid I've been thinking

448
00:30:49,391 --> 00:30:51,018
♪ A dangerous pastime

449
00:30:51,059 --> 00:30:52,227
♪ I know

450
00:30:52,311 --> 00:30:55,606
♪ But that wacky old coot
♪ is Belle's father

451
00:30:55,689 --> 00:30:58,817
♪ And his sanity's only so-so

452
00:30:58,942 --> 00:31:02,154
♪ Now, the wheels in my head
♪ have been turning

453
00:31:02,237 --> 00:31:05,365
♪ Since I looked at that loony old man

454
00:31:05,407 --> 00:31:08,869
♪ See, I promised myself
♪ I'd be married to Belle

455
00:31:08,911 --> 00:31:13,457
♪ And right now, I'm evolving a plan

456
00:31:13,582 --> 00:31:15,667
-If I...
-Yes?

457
00:31:15,751 --> 00:31:18,754
-Then we...
-No, would she?

458
00:31:18,837 --> 00:31:20,464
-Guess.
-Now I get it!

459
00:31:20,547 --> 00:31:22,799
-Let's go!
-Let's go!

460
00:31:22,883 --> 00:31:26,929
♪ No one plots like Gaston

461
00:31:26,970 --> 00:31:28,597
♪ Takes cheap shots like Gaston

462
00:31:28,680 --> 00:31:31,975
♪ Plans to persecute harmless crackpots
♪ like Gaston

463
00:31:32,059 --> 00:31:37,648
♪ So, his marriage
♪ we soon will be celebrating

464
00:31:37,731 --> 00:31:40,275
♪ My, what a guy

465
00:31:40,317 --> 00:31:44,571
[L]♪ Gaston

466
00:31:47,783 --> 00:31:50,410
Will no one help me?

467
00:31:59,169 --> 00:32:01,380
-Who is it?
-Mrs. Potts, dear.

468
00:32:03,465 --> 00:32:05,425
I thought you might like a spot of tea.

469
00:32:05,467 --> 00:32:07,469
But you're... You're a...

470
00:32:09,304 --> 00:32:11,515
-Careful.
-This is impossible.

471
00:32:11,598 --> 00:32:14,226
I know it is, but here we are.

472
00:32:14,309 --> 00:32:17,145
I told you she was pretty, Mama,
didn't I?

473
00:32:17,187 --> 00:32:21,483
All right, Chip, now, that'll do.
Slowly now. Don't spill.

474
00:32:22,985 --> 00:32:24,403
Thank you.

475
00:32:24,486 --> 00:32:26,446
Wanna see me do a trick?

476
00:32:27,865 --> 00:32:30,909
-Chip!
-Sorry.

477
00:32:30,993 --> 00:32:33,579
That was a very brave thing
you did, my dear.

478
00:32:33,662 --> 00:32:35,122
We all think so.

479
00:32:35,163 --> 00:32:38,709
But I've lost my father,
my dreams, everything.

480
00:32:38,792 --> 00:32:43,463
Cheer up, child.
It'll turn out all right in the end.

481
00:32:43,505 --> 00:32:45,132
You'll see.

482
00:32:45,174 --> 00:32:46,842
Listen to me jabbering on

483
00:32:46,884 --> 00:32:49,052
while there's a supper
to get on the table.

484
00:32:49,136 --> 00:32:50,929
Chip?

485
00:32:51,013 --> 00:32:52,347
Bye.

486
00:32:52,389 --> 00:32:55,559
Well, now,
what shall we dress you in for dinner?

487
00:32:55,642 --> 00:32:58,562
Let's see what I got in my drawers.

488
00:32:58,645 --> 00:33:00,355
How embarrassing!

489
00:33:02,900 --> 00:33:06,236
Here we are.
You'll look ravishing in this one.

490
00:33:06,320 --> 00:33:09,698
That's very kind of you,
but I'm not going to dinner.

491
00:33:10,365 --> 00:33:11,867
But you must.

492
00:33:15,037 --> 00:33:17,497
Dinner is served.

493
00:33:19,750 --> 00:33:21,668
What's taking so long?

494
00:33:21,710 --> 00:33:23,462
I told her to come down.

495
00:33:23,545 --> 00:33:27,049
-Why isn't she here yet?
-Try to be patient, sir.

496
00:33:27,132 --> 00:33:30,469
The girl has lost her father
and her freedom all in one day.

497
00:33:30,552 --> 00:33:32,054
Master, have you thought

498
00:33:32,095 --> 00:33:34,932
that perhaps this girl could be the one
to break the spell?

499
00:33:35,015 --> 00:33:37,809
Of course I have! I'm not a fool.

500
00:33:37,893 --> 00:33:40,646
Good! So, you fall in love with her,

501
00:33:40,729 --> 00:33:44,358
she falls in love with you, and poof!
The spell is broken.

502
00:33:44,399 --> 00:33:46,652
We'll be human again by midnight.

503
00:33:46,735 --> 00:33:49,238
It's not that easy, Lumiere.
These things take time.

504
00:33:49,279 --> 00:33:51,949
But the rose has already begun to wilt.

505
00:33:52,032 --> 00:33:53,909
It's no use.

506
00:33:53,951 --> 00:33:56,411
She's so beautiful and I'm...

507
00:33:56,453 --> 00:33:58,080
Well, look at me!

508
00:34:00,207 --> 00:34:03,210
You must help her to see past all that.

509
00:34:03,252 --> 00:34:05,045
I don't know how.

510
00:34:05,087 --> 00:34:07,673
Well, you can start
by making yourself more presentable.

511
00:34:07,756 --> 00:34:10,092
Straighten up.
Try to act like a gentleman.

512
00:34:10,175 --> 00:34:14,096
Yes. When she comes in,
give her a dashing, debonair smile.

513
00:34:14,179 --> 00:34:16,514
Come, come, show me the smile.

514
00:34:16,598 --> 00:34:20,561
-But don't frighten the poor girl.
-Impress her with your rapier wit.

515
00:34:20,601 --> 00:34:21,770
But be gentle.

516
00:34:21,853 --> 00:34:24,147
-Shower her with compliments.
-But be sincere.

517
00:34:24,231 --> 00:34:25,690
And above all,

518
00:34:25,774 --> 00:34:28,777
-you must control your temper!
-You must control your temper!

519
00:34:28,819 --> 00:34:30,237
Here she is!

520
00:34:32,281 --> 00:34:33,782
Good evening.

521
00:34:34,699 --> 00:34:37,536
-Well, where is she?
-Who?

522
00:34:38,954 --> 00:34:41,331
The girl, yes. The girl.

523
00:34:41,415 --> 00:34:45,293
Well, actually, she's in the process of...

524
00:34:45,377 --> 00:34:49,797
Circumstances being what they are...
She's not coming.

525
00:34:50,924 --> 00:34:52,009
What?

526
00:34:52,634 --> 00:34:55,179
Oh, dear. Your Grace! Your Eminence!

527
00:34:55,929 --> 00:34:57,639
[L]Let's not be hasty!

528
00:35:00,642 --> 00:35:02,394
I thought I told you
to come down to dinner!

529
00:35:02,477 --> 00:35:03,979
I'm not hungry.

530
00:35:04,521 --> 00:35:07,816
You'll come out or I'll... I'll...
I'll break down the door!

531
00:35:07,900 --> 00:35:09,776
Master, I could be wrong,

532
00:35:09,818 --> 00:35:14,364
but that may not be the best way
to win the girl's affections.

533
00:35:14,448 --> 00:35:17,826
Please attempt to be a gentleman.

534
00:35:17,910 --> 00:35:20,662
But she is being so difficult.

535
00:35:20,704 --> 00:35:23,081
Gently, gently.

536
00:35:25,125 --> 00:35:27,544
-Will you come down to dinner?
-No!

537
00:35:28,837 --> 00:35:31,173
Suave, genteel.

538
00:35:31,215 --> 00:35:34,176
It would give me great pleasure

539
00:35:35,093 --> 00:35:37,095
if you would join me for dinner.

540
00:35:37,179 --> 00:35:38,847
And we say "please."

541
00:35:39,223 --> 00:35:40,724
-Please.
-No, thank you.

542
00:35:40,807 --> 00:35:43,018
-You can't stay in there forever!
-Yes, I can.

543
00:35:43,101 --> 00:35:47,648
Fine! Then go ahead and starve!

544
00:35:47,689 --> 00:35:52,361
If she doesn't eat with me,
then she doesn't eat at all!

545
00:35:55,822 --> 00:35:58,825
Oh, dear.
That didn't go very well at all, did it?

546
00:35:58,867 --> 00:36:01,745
Lumiere, stand watch at the door

547
00:36:01,828 --> 00:36:05,123
and inform me at once
if there is the slightest change.

548
00:36:05,207 --> 00:36:07,709
You can count on me, mon capitaine.

549
00:36:07,751 --> 00:36:11,964
Well, we might as well go downstairs
and start cleaning up.

550
00:36:13,382 --> 00:36:15,634
I ask nicely, but she refuses.

551
00:36:16,343 --> 00:36:18,720
What does she want me to do, beg?

552
00:36:19,972 --> 00:36:21,598
Show me the girl.

553
00:36:23,725 --> 00:36:27,396
But the master's really not so bad,
once you get to know him.

554
00:36:27,479 --> 00:36:29,523
Why don't you give him a chance?

555
00:36:29,565 --> 00:36:31,400
I don't want to get to know him.

556
00:36:31,441 --> 00:36:34,403
I don't want to have anything
to do with him.

557
00:36:36,196 --> 00:36:38,115
I'm just fooling myself.

558
00:36:38,198 --> 00:36:41,076
She'll never see me as anything

559
00:36:41,159 --> 00:36:42,703
but a monster.

560
00:36:47,916 --> 00:36:49,418
It's hopeless.

561
00:37:07,311 --> 00:37:09,146
-Oh, no.
-Oh, yes.

562
00:37:09,229 --> 00:37:11,940
-Oh, no.
-Oh, yes, yes, yes.

563
00:37:11,982 --> 00:37:14,443
I've been burned by you before.

564
00:37:17,613 --> 00:37:19,698
Zut alors! She has emerged!

565
00:37:24,286 --> 00:37:28,290
Come on, Chip. Into the cupboard
with your brothers and sisters.

566
00:37:29,374 --> 00:37:31,043
But I'm not sleepy.

567
00:37:31,126 --> 00:37:34,171
-Yes, you are.
-No, I'm not.

568
00:37:34,254 --> 00:37:37,799
I work and I slave all day long,
and for what?

569
00:37:37,883 --> 00:37:40,802
A culinary masterpiece gone to waste!

570
00:37:40,886 --> 00:37:43,931
Stop your grousing.
It's been a long night for all of us.

571
00:37:43,972 --> 00:37:47,142
Well, if you ask me,
she was just being stubborn.

572
00:37:47,226 --> 00:37:48,810
After all, he did say "please."

573
00:37:48,894 --> 00:37:51,647
But if the master doesn't learn
to control that temper,

574
00:37:51,730 --> 00:37:53,982
-he'll never break the...
-Splendid to see you

575
00:37:54,066 --> 00:37:55,734
out and about, mademoiselle.

576
00:37:55,817 --> 00:37:58,445
I am Cogsworth, head of the household.

577
00:38:00,864 --> 00:38:03,909
-This is Lumiere.
-Enchanté, chérie.

578
00:38:03,992 --> 00:38:07,162
If there's, stop that,
anything we, please,

579
00:38:07,246 --> 00:38:10,457
can do to make your stay
more comfortable...

580
00:38:10,499 --> 00:38:12,835
-I am a little hungry.
-You are?

581
00:38:12,918 --> 00:38:14,670
Hear that? She's hungry.

582
00:38:14,753 --> 00:38:17,840
Stoke the fire.
Break out the silver. Wake the china.

583
00:38:17,923 --> 00:38:20,592
Remember what the master said.

584
00:38:20,676 --> 00:38:23,679
Pish tosh. I'm not about
to let the poor child go hungry.

585
00:38:23,762 --> 00:38:26,682
All right, fine. Glass of water,
crust of bread and then...

586
00:38:26,765 --> 00:38:28,684
[L]Cogsworth, I am surprised at you.

587
00:38:29,351 --> 00:38:32,062
She's not a prisoner. She's our guest.

588
00:38:32,145 --> 00:38:35,774
We must make her feel welcome here.
Right this way, mademoiselle.

589
00:38:35,858 --> 00:38:37,693
Well, keep it down.

590
00:38:37,734 --> 00:38:40,195
If the master finds out about this,
it will be our necks.

591
00:38:40,237 --> 00:38:42,072
Of course, of course.

592
00:38:42,155 --> 00:38:45,158
But what is dinner
without a little music?

593
00:38:45,868 --> 00:38:47,035
Music?

594
00:38:50,956 --> 00:38:54,459
It is with deepest pride
and greatest pleasure

595
00:38:54,543 --> 00:38:56,378
that we welcome you tonight.

596
00:38:56,420 --> 00:38:59,047
And now, we invite you to relax.

597
00:38:59,131 --> 00:39:04,011
Let us pull up a chair,
