00:42:27,464 --> 00:42:30,801
-Bravo! That was wonderful.
-Thank you.

681
00:42:31,760 --> 00:42:36,265
Thank you, mademoiselle.
Good show, wasn't it? Everyone!

682
00:42:37,182 --> 00:42:41,687
My goodness, look at the time.
Now it's off to bed, off to bed.

683
00:42:41,770 --> 00:42:44,147
I couldn't possibly go to bed now.

684
00:42:44,231 --> 00:42:46,191
It's my first time in an enchanted castle.

685
00:42:46,275 --> 00:42:47,609
Enchanted!

686
00:42:48,485 --> 00:42:51,655
Who said anything
about the castle being enchanted?

687
00:42:51,738 --> 00:42:53,323
It was you, wasn't it?

688
00:42:53,407 --> 00:42:55,534
I figured it out for myself.

689
00:42:57,369 --> 00:42:59,788
I'd like to look around,
if that's all right.

690
00:43:00,455 --> 00:43:02,958
-Would you like a tour?
-Wait a second. Wait a second.

691
00:43:03,041 --> 00:43:05,502
I'm not sure that's such a good idea.

692
00:43:05,586 --> 00:43:09,298
We can't let her go poking around
in certain places,

693
00:43:09,423 --> 00:43:10,841
if you know what I mean.

694
00:43:10,924 --> 00:43:12,384
Perhaps you'd like to take me.

695
00:43:12,467 --> 00:43:15,846
I'm sure you know everything there is
to know about the castle.

696
00:43:15,929 --> 00:43:18,807
Well. Actually, I...

697
00:43:18,891 --> 00:43:20,225
Yes, I do.

698
00:43:21,435 --> 00:43:25,022
As you can see,
the pseudo-facade was stripped away

699
00:43:25,063 --> 00:43:27,524
to reveal the minimalist Rococo design.

700
00:43:27,608 --> 00:43:30,319
Note the unusual
inverted vaulted ceilings.

701
00:43:30,402 --> 00:43:34,072
This is yet another example
of the late-neoclassic Baroque period.

702
00:43:34,156 --> 00:43:37,659
And, as I always say,
if it's not Baroque, don't fix it.

703
00:43:40,329 --> 00:43:41,747
Where was I?

704
00:43:42,664 --> 00:43:44,082
As you were!

705
00:43:44,917 --> 00:43:49,588
Now, then, if I may draw your attention
to the flying buttresses above the...

706
00:43:49,671 --> 00:43:50,672
[L]Mademoiselle?

707
00:43:56,803 --> 00:43:59,181
-What's up there?
-Where? There? Nothing.

708
00:43:59,264 --> 00:44:01,350
Absolutely nothing of interest at all
in the west wing.

709
00:44:01,433 --> 00:44:03,435
Dusty, dull, very boring.

710
00:44:04,603 --> 00:44:06,939
So, that's the west wing!

711
00:44:07,022 --> 00:44:08,357
Nice going.

712
00:44:09,024 --> 00:44:11,568
I wonder what he's hiding up there.

713
00:44:11,652 --> 00:44:15,572
-Hiding? The master is hiding nothing.
-Then it wouldn't be forbidden.

714
00:44:15,656 --> 00:44:20,077
Perhaps mademoiselle would like
to see something else?

715
00:44:20,160 --> 00:44:22,788
We have exquisite tapestries
dating all the way back to...

716
00:44:22,871 --> 00:44:25,040
-Maybe later.
-The gardens.

717
00:44:25,082 --> 00:44:27,251
Or... Or the... The library, perhaps?

718
00:44:27,334 --> 00:44:29,211
You have a library?

719
00:44:29,294 --> 00:44:31,380
-Yes. Indeed.
-With books.

720
00:44:31,421 --> 00:44:33,882
-Scads of books.
-Mountains of books.

721
00:44:33,966 --> 00:44:35,384
-Forests of books.
-Cascades.

722
00:44:35,467 --> 00:44:37,052
-Cloudbursts.
-Swamps of books.

723
00:44:37,094 --> 00:44:39,763
More books than you'll ever be able
to read in a lifetime.

724
00:44:39,847 --> 00:44:41,932
Books on every subject ever studied

725
00:44:42,015 --> 00:44:44,810
by every author
who ever set pen to paper.

726
00:46:24,826 --> 00:46:28,205
-Why did you come here?
-I'm... I'm sorry.

727
00:46:28,288 --> 00:46:32,000
-I warned you never to come here!
-I didn't mean any harm.

728
00:46:32,084 --> 00:46:34,795
Do you realize
what you could have done?

729
00:46:35,671 --> 00:46:37,047
Please! Stop!

730
00:46:37,130 --> 00:46:39,341
-Get out!
-No!

731
00:46:41,510 --> 00:46:44,555
Get out!

732
00:46:55,983 --> 00:46:57,109
Where are you going?

733
00:46:57,192 --> 00:47:00,487
Promise or no promise,
I can't stay here another minute.

734
00:47:00,529 --> 00:47:03,156
No, wait, please! Please, wait!

735
00:48:19,274 --> 00:48:20,275
No!

736
00:49:30,470 --> 00:49:32,556
Here, now. Don't do that.

737
00:49:36,768 --> 00:49:38,437
Just hold still.

738
00:49:40,230 --> 00:49:41,356
That hurts!

739
00:49:41,398 --> 00:49:43,358
If you'd hold still,
it wouldn't hurt as much!

740
00:49:43,400 --> 00:49:45,611
Well, if you hadn't have run away,
this wouldn't have happened.

741
00:49:45,694 --> 00:49:49,114
If you hadn't frightened me,
I wouldn't have run away.

742
00:49:49,615 --> 00:49:52,201
Well, you shouldn't have been
in the west wing!

743
00:49:52,284 --> 00:49:55,287
Well, you should learn
to control your temper.

744
00:49:58,123 --> 00:50:01,043
Now, hold still.
This might sting a little.

745
00:50:04,338 --> 00:50:08,509
By the way,
thank you for saving my life.

746
00:50:13,180 --> 00:50:14,723
You're welcome.

747
00:50:21,730 --> 00:50:26,068
I don't usually leave the asylum
in the middle of the night,

748
00:50:26,109 --> 00:50:28,862
but he said
you'd make it worth my while.

749
